{
  "local_port": 37850,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best Bank robbery movies?",
  "response": "Bank robbery movies have long been a staple of the crime genre, offering thrilling heists, complex characters, and intense action. Here\u2019s a list of some of the best bank robbery movies that have captivated audiences:\n\n### Classic and Iconic Bank Robbery Movies:\n1. **Heat (1995)**  \n   Directed by Michael Mann, this film features Robert De Niro and Al Pacino in a gripping tale of professional thieves and the detectives pursuing them. Its iconic bank heist scene is legendary.\n\n2. **Dog Day Afternoon (1975)**  \n   Directed by Sidney Lumet and starring Al Pacino, this film is based on a real-life bank robbery turned hostage situation. It\u2019s a tense and character-driven drama.\n\n3. **The Town (2010)**  \n   Directed by and starring Ben Affleck, this film follows a group of bank robbers in Boston. It\u2019s known for its intense action and emotional depth.\n\n4. **Inside Man (2006)**  \n   Directed by Spike Lee and starring Denzel Washington, Clive Owen, and Jodie Foster, this clever heist thriller keeps viewers guessing until the very end.\n\n5. **Point Break (1991)**  \n   Directed by Kathryn Bigelow, this film features Patrick Swayze and Keanu Reeves in a story about a bank-robbing surf gang. It\u2019s an adrenaline-packed action classic.\n\n6. **Bonnie and Clyde (1967)**  \n   Directed by Arthur Penn, this film romanticizes the infamous bank-robbing duo and their crime spree during the Great Depression.\n\n### Modern and Gripping Bank Robbery Movies:\n7. **Baby Driver (2017)**  \n   Directed by Edgar Wright, this film combines high-octane car chases with a bank heist plot, all set to a killer soundtrack.\n\n8. **The Bank Job (2008)**  \n   Inspired by true events, this British heist film starring Jason Statham is a tense and entertaining take on a 1971 robbery.\n\n9. **Hell or High Water (2016)**  \n   A modern Western about two brothers trying to save their family ranch by robbing banks, starring Chris Pine and Ben Foster.\n\n10. **The Italian Job (1969 & 2003)**  \n   Both versions of this film\u2014the original with Michael Caine and the remake with Mark Wahlberg\u2014are beloved for their creative heists and Mini Cooper chases.\n\n### Underrated Gems:\n11. **Set It Off (1996)**  \n   A gritty and emotional film about four women who turn to bank robbery to escape their difficult lives.\n\n12. **A Fish Called Wanda (1988)**  \n   A dark comedy about a bungled diamond heist that involves multiple double-crosses and hilarious chaos.\n\n13. **The Lookout (2007)**  \n   Directed by Scott Frank, this underrated heist film stars Joseph Gordon-Levitt as a brain-damaged janitor drawn into a bank robbery plot.\n\n### International Bank Robbery Movies:\n14. **Rififi (1955)**  \n   A French classic about a meticulously planned jewelry heist, featuring one of the most famous silent heist sequences in cinema.\n\n15. **The Killing (1956)**  \n   Directed by Stanley Kubrick, this film is a tightly plotted noir about a meticulously planned racetrack robbery.\n\nThese films offer a mix of suspense, action, and character-driven storytelling, making them must-watches for fans of the heist genre.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
